Review: Saw this earlier today and the score is still stuck in my head. I can already tell it’s gonna be there for weeks. I love everything about this The cinematography, the production design, the performances, the dialogue It all comes together flawlessly
Such a deeply loving attention to detail in this movie For example, all the birds shit all over the place just like real birds
I like the part where Godzilla did the blue spine thing and did the roar He had a cool roar I like when Godzilla roared
Don’t look at the plot summary, don’t look at the poster, and for the love of fucking god do not under any circumstances watch the trailer
Unironically one of Adam Sandler’s top five performances (Just because basically everything besides Uncut Gems and Punch Drunk Love is total garbage)

This made so much fucking money and Nintendo is unquestionably going to leverage that into making their own cinematic universe so now we all have to prepare for a world where we’re getting two or three of these abortions per year
Joel Edgerton’s ass got some screen time so at least this slog wasn’t a total waste
The score is lovely, the cinematography is gorgeous and it’s so so so so fucking pretentious it was almost admirableAlmost
I wasn’t expecting to love this as much as I did when I was a kid but I also wasn’t expecting it to be one of the most irritating and unpleasant movies I’ve ever sat through

Nic Cage’s best work since Adaptation The dream sequences were all super fun, well executed, and in some cases traumatizing I was loving this movie until about the last 20 minutes which contained one particularly bad scene that feels like an SNL skit
What a genius subversion of audience expectations to make a movie with zero sense of narrative build-up and the lamest climax in the history of cinema Good job, David
This is either the straightest gay smut I’ve ever seen or the gayest straight smut I’ve ever seen. Either way not quite smutty enough to satisfy a psychopath like myself
